## Implementation Plan

### Problem
The default `release.yml` config (used when no `.github/release.yml` exists)
was missing several conventional commit types from the "Internal Changes"
category, causing them to fall through to the unlabelled "Other" section.

Missing types: `test`, `tests`, `style`

### Approach
Update the regex alternation group in `DEFAULT_RELEASE_CONFIG` in
`src/utils/changelog.ts` to include the missing types:
- `tests?` — matches both `test:` and `tests:` in one token
- `style` — code style changes (whitespace, formatting, semicolons)

### Changes
1. `src/utils/changelog.ts` — Updated the "Internal Changes" commit_patterns
   regex: added `tests?|style` to the alternation group alongside the
   existing `build|refactor|meta|chore|ci|ref|perf`.

2. `docs/src/content/docs/configuration.md` — Matching update to the
   default config YAML example shown in the documentation.

3. `src/utils/__tests__/changelog-utils.test.ts` — Updated the test that
   was hardcoding the old pattern; renamed the test description and added
   three new assertions covering `test:`, `tests:`, and `style:`.
